interactions.lmstext: Individuals with Marfan syndrome have mutations in a gene involved in collagen production. They often develop aortic aneurisms. What layer of the arterial wall is most affected by this mutation?
In which layer of the heart wall are the major components of the conducting system of the heart located?

choices.lmstext: the lamina propria of the endothelial layer

interactions.lmstext: Which layer of the heart wall produces pericardial fluid?

choices.lmstext: the lamina propria of the endothelial layer

interactions.lmstext: In which layer of the heart wall are nociceptive nerve endings that respond to ischemia primarily located?

choices.lmstext: the lamina propria of the endothelial layer
